><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>
The rule of the golden mean does not apply to
the last end. "Every art seeks the end to infinity,
wishing to secure it to the utmost; but the means not
to infinity, for the end in view limits all arts" 
(Aristotle, <i>Politics</i>, I, x, 13).

